Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.model

Class WarehouseDepots

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.common.utils.observe.MessageObservable
it.polimi.ingsw.server.model.WarehouseDepots
public class WarehouseDepots
extends MessageObservable
Class that represents the warehouse of the personal board. This class coordinates the depots where resources from the market are stored

  • Method Details

    • add

      public void add​(int depotNumber, java.util.Map<Resource,​java.lang.Integer> singleResourceMap) throws InvalidAdditionException
      Method used to add a given quantity of a resource to a specified depot
      Parameters:
      depotNumber - The depot to which the resource has to be added, the specified depot must exist
      singleResourceMap - The map must contain only one resource and the value associated with the resource is the quantity that will be added
      Throws:
      InvalidAdditionException - "Invalid Depot" : the depot does not exist "Not one resource": singleResourceMap does not contain only one resource "Same resource in other depots": when trying to add a resource to a standard depot and the same resource is in another standard depot The exception can be thrown by the depot itself when there is not enough space or there is already another resource in the depot

    • addSpecialDepot

      public void addSpecialDepot​(Resource resource)
      Method to add a special depot
      Parameters:
      resource - The only type of resource that can be added to the special depot

    • getNumDepots

      public int getNumDepots()
      Method to get how many depots there are in warehouse depots
      Returns:
      The number of depots in warehouse depots

    • swap

      public void swap​(int depotNumber1, int depotNumber2) throws InvalidSwapException
      Method used to swap resources between two standard depots
      Parameters:
      depotNumber1 - Cannot be a special depot
      depotNumber2 - Cannot be a special depot
      Throws:
      InvalidSwapException - This exception is thrown when the depot is a special depot or when the resource of at least one depot do not fit the other depot

    • moveToFromSpecialDepot

      public void moveToFromSpecialDepot​(int sourceDepotNumber, int destinationDepotNumber, int quantity) throws InvalidRemovalException, InvalidAdditionException, InvalidMoveException
      Method to move a resource between a standard depot and a special depot, only one of the two depots can be a special depot
      Parameters:
      sourceDepotNumber - Number of the depot from which the resource has to be moved, if this is a special depot the other depot cannot be a special depot
      destinationDepotNumber - Number of the depot to which the resource has to be moved, if this is a special depot the other depot cannot be a special depot
      quantity - How much of the resource in the source depot has to be moved
      Throws:
      InvalidRemovalException - If there is not enough of the resource in the source depot
      InvalidAdditionException - If the resource cannot be moved to the destination depot
      InvalidMoveException - If the condition that only one of the two depots can be a special depot is not respected or if at least one of the two depots does not exist

    • isAvailable

      public boolean isAvailable​(java.util.Map<Resource,​java.lang.Integer> resourceMap)
      Checks that all the resources and their quantities in resourceMap are stored in WarehouseDepot
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      true if all the resources in resourceMap are in WareHouseDepot, false otherwise

    • resourcesNotAvailable
